<https://www.gov.uk/government/people/john-healey> <http://ogp.me/ns#description> "John Healey was appointed Secretary of State for Defence on 5 July 2024. He was elected as the MP for Rawmarsh and Conisbrough in July 2024. He was Shadow Housing Secretary from 2015 to 2020 and Shadow Health Secretary from 2010-2011. During Labour’s time in Government, John was PPS to the Chancellor of the Exchequer from 1999-2001 and a Minister from 2001-2010, serving successively as Adult Skills Minister, Treasury Minister, Local Government Minister and Housing Minister. Before entering Parliament, John was Campaigns Director at the Trades Union Congress and a disability rights campaigner. John is married with one son and lives in Rotherham."@en <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/rdfa> .
